    "summary": "Importance weights for translator profile factors",
    "content": "1: 10 -- Non-negotiable. Misreading the source destroys everything downstream.\n2: 9 -- The text IS philosophy. A literary-only translator will miss what is at stake.\n3: 8 -- The author's voice (personal, exploratory, sometimes playful) must survive translation.\n4: 7 -- Essential for Essays 6-7, less relevant for the others. Can be partially handled by expert consultation, but the translator must at minimum be able to typeset and proofread LaTeX notation without introducing errors.\n5: 9 -- The register range in this collection is unusually wide (magic book fairy tales to category-theoretic formalism to classical Chinese quotation). A translator who can only do one register will produce an incoherent collection.\n6: 7 -- Important for 后形而上学 整理 specifically. The author explicitly warns that their usage diverges from tradition, so the translator must know the conventions well enough to signal departures. But this can be supplemented by our chinese-phil-expert's report.\n7: 8 -- Load-bearing for the Sisyphus/cat essay, the Dao-De-Ren-Yi-Li reversal, and the magic book narratives. Without this, the philosophical content of those passages is lost.\n8: 6 -- Useful but supplementable. Standard renderings of Dasein, Entzauberung, Lebenswelt, etc. are well-documented. Our expert reports provide the mappings. The translator needs to know enough to use the conventions correctly but does not need deep expertise.\n9: 4 -- Limited relevance. Buddhist concepts appear only peripherally. The parallel to Nagarjuna that I noted in my report is my analysis, not the author's explicit engagement. A brief consultation with the buddhism-expert suffices.\n10: 6 -- Similar to point 8. Kantian terminology is well-standardized in English. The author's framework parallels Kant but does not use Kantian vocabulary directly, so the translator needs awareness, not mastery.\n11: 3 -- Lowest priority. The author does not engage with analytic philosophy of language directly. The Wittgenstein connection is present but mediated through the category-theoretic framework, which is a different register entirely.\n"
